TITLE: China is walking a 'very slender path' with Russia's invasion of Ukraine, expert says
SUMMARY: One military expert says that China is walking a "very slender path" in terms of how it's approaching Russia's invasion of Ukraine, and is predicting it will be very difficult for the country to stay neutral in the conflict the longer it goes on.

TITLE: WaPo columnist says Biden's call for regime change was deliberate, not a 'gaffe,' despite WH walk-back
SUMMARY: Washington Post columnist rejects the media's use of the word "gaffe" in reference to President Biden's recent call for a regime change in Russia.

TITLE: March Madness 2022: North Carolina takes big lead into halftime against Saint Peter's
SUMMARY: North Carolina capitalized on a lengthy Saint Peter’s shooting slump to take a lead into the locker room in the first half of their Elite Eight matchup on Sunday night 38-19.

TITLE: Miley Cyrus breaks down in tears during her tribute performance to Taylor Hawkins
SUMMARY: Miley Cyrus got emotional during a tribute performance for her late friend, Taylor Hawkins, at Lollapalooza Brazil on Saturday.

TITLE: Jimmy Garoppolo could be flat-out cut by 49ers
SUMMARY: The San Francisco 49ers are in a bind with quarterback Jimmy Garoppolo, who has a $25 million compensation package and is recovering from surgery he had to repair the labrum in his throwing shoulder.

TITLE: Kyrie Irving: People dealing with 'real consequences' from being unvaccinated
SUMMARY: No player in the NBA faced the daunting reality of vaccine restrictions like Brooklyn’s Kyrie Irving.

TITLE: Atlantic writer slams CNN for quoting Biden’s call for Putin to be removed from power
SUMMARY: Tom Nichols, contributing writer of The Atlantic, criticized CNN for quoting President Biden’s call for regime change in Russia.

TITLE: Florida amusement park horror: Dollywood closes drop tower ride made by same manufacturer as Orlando FreeFall
SUMMARY: Dollywood is closing one of their rides which was developed from the same manufacturer as the Orlando FreeFall ride in Orlando, Florida, where one teenager fell off and died on Thursday night.

TITLE: March Madness 2022: Kansas blows past Miami in 2nd half, reaches 16th Final Four
SUMMARY: Kansas (32-6), the only No. 1 seed left in the NCAA Tournament, won the Midwest Region for the 13th time with its ninth consecutive victory overall.

TITLE: Russia and Ukraine to start next round of live negotiations in Turkey in the coming days
SUMMARY: Ukrainian and Russian officials will meet on Monday in Istanbul, Turkey, for the next round of in-person peace talks, a Ukrainian negotiator said Sunday.

TITLE: Verstappen passes LeClerc late to win Formula one Saudi Arabian Grand Prix
Frank Reich says Matt Ryan, Colts 'needed each other'
SUMMARY: Nearly a week after trading for quarterback Matt Ryan, Indianapolis Colts head coach Frank Reich says the 2016 NFL MVP and his new team “needed each other."

TITLE: NY lieutenant governor the focus of federal campaign fraud probe: Report
SUMMARY: Federal investigators have reportedly issued subpoenas to the New York Senate and former campaign advisers of New York Lt. Gov. Brian Benjamin, trying to determine whether he had a hand in funneling fraudulent donations to his failed 2021 campaign.

TITLE: Sen. Rubio reveals 'likeliest' scenario regarding Russia's use of chemical, biological weapons
SUMMARY: Sen. Marco Rubio, R-Fla., argued that the “likeliest thing you are going to see” from Russian President Vladimir Putin is trying to use chemical or biological weapons “in a way that makes it look like someone else did it.”

TITLE: NBC News correspondent says Zelenskyy not 'overly impressed' by Biden's comments on Putin
SUMMARY: NBC News chief foreign correspondent Richard Engel said he didn't think Zelenskyy was "overly impressed" with Biden's comments on Putin in Poland.

TITLE: Zelenskyy: West needs more courage in helping Ukraine fight
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy accused the West of cowardice as his country fights to stave off Russia’s invading troops, making an exasperated plea for fighter jets and tanks to sustain a defense as the war ground into a battle of attrition.

TITLE: Saint Peter's coach Shaheen Holloway tweets inspirational passage before Elite Eight game: 'Stay the course'
SUMMARY: Saint Peter’s men’s basketball coach Shaheen Holloway tweeted some wisdom on Sunday hours before his Peacocks tip off against North Carolina in the Elite Eight.

TITLE: 'Fox News Sunday' on March 27, 2022
SUMMARY: "Fox News Sunday" welcomed guests Julianne Smith, Rick Scott and Ro Khanna.

TITLE: Hearst Castle, national landmark in California, gets reopening date after 2-year closure
SUMMARY: The Hearst San Simeon State Historical Monument in California is set to reopen to the public after the coronavirus pandemic and “severe rainstorms” forced the tourist destination to shut its doors for over two years.

TITLE: Memphis men’s basketball accused of several NCAA violations
SUMMARY: The University of Memphis is accused of several violations stemming from a lengthy investigation into the men's basketball program, according to multiple reports.
